{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f5f5937-43f5-4063-98da-68fb1c020b7c","content":"Here's my analysis:\n\n## `ResolveProjectReferences` is NOT the real bottleneck — it's a misleading metric.\n\n**Why the 70% figure is deceptive:**\n\n`ResolveProjectReferences` doesn't just \"resolve\" references — it *builds* the referenced projects (LibA, LibB) if they're out of date. The time you're seeing is actually the compilation of LibA and LibB, rolled up under this target name. It's doing useful, unavoidable work.\n\n**Your dependency graph:**\n```\nApp → LibA\nApp → LibB → LibA\n```\n\nThis is a tiny 3-project solution. MSBuild already builds LibA once (shared), then LibB, then App. There's very little to optimize here.\n\n**Verdict on the proposed ideas:**\n\n| Idea | Assessment |\n|------|-----------|\n| Replace with NuGet packages | Adds packaging overhead; only worthwhile for large shared libs across repos |\n| Skip/override the target | **Will break your build** — downstream outputs won't be available |\n| Consolidate into one project | Removes modularity for negligible gain at this scale |\n\n**What to actually focus on:**\n\n1. **Incremental builds** — ensure you're not doing clean builds every time. MSBuild skips up-to-date projects automatically.\n2. **Build parallelism** — use `dotnet build -m` (already default). LibA and LibB can build in parallel since LibB depends on LibA but App depends on both.\n3. **If the solution grows** — look at `BuildInParallel`, the `/graph` switch (`dotnet build -graph`), and whether `LibA` really needs to be a separate project.\n\n**TL;DR:** The target is expensive because it *is* the build of your dependencies. That's not a bottleneck — that's the work itself. Optimize the referenced projects' compile time, not the resolution mechanism.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"84894cac-2d12-47ee-8958-bb393522be09","outputTokens":447,"requestId":"EC1A:188DB0:DF1E29:1160CF1:6A012EBB"},"id":"f69150f9-570f-4fbe-a853-77bd743e9acb","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:20:07.835Z","parentId":"349e36e9-ab23-4d55-8e78-04428d95d1aa"}
